description:
Uganda and Kenya share two things––a border and some of the world’s finest coffee. Up until recently, Ugandan beans were overlooked in favor of Ethiopian and Kenyan, as coffee-growing in Uganda was still in its infancy. But in the past decade, the country has started to shine, and coffee bean importers have noticed.


This bean is grown on Mount Elgon’s farms––about 1,650-2,200 meters in altitude. They’re traditionally washed and patio-dried to produce a decadent, earthy flavor. 


Cupping Notes: Sweet floral brown sugar vanilla honey aroma, well balanced intense flavor, clean sweet fruity rich aftertaste, smooth medium body and bright crisp winey acidity with citrus, lemon, orange, lemon, lime, peach, pear and pomegranate notes


Try before you stock up with a 1/2 pound sample!


Cupping Score 2025 Uganda Mt Elgon A, Bugisu

